Kubernetes Troubleshooting Commands (MUST MEMORIZE)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Cluster & Nodes
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node-name>
kubectl get componentstatuses


Check:

Node Ready / NotReady

DiskPressure / MemoryPressure

SchedulingDisabled

2Ô∏è‚É£ Pod-Level Troubleshooting (MOST IMPORTANT)
Pod Status
kubectl get pods -A
kubectl get pod <pod-name> -o wide

Pod Details (First Command in Any Issue)
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>


Look for:

Events

Scheduling errors

Image pull errors

Probe failures

3Ô∏è‚É£ Logs (Application Issues)
kubectl logs <pod-name>
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous
kubectl logs <pod-name> -c <container-name>


Use when:

CrashLoopBackOff

App crashes

DB connection issues

4Ô∏è‚É£ Scheduling Issues (Pod Pending)
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node-name>
kubectl get pvc


Check:

Resource availability

Node affinity / taints

PVC bound or not

5Ô∏è‚É£ Image Issues
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
kubectl get secret


Check:

Image name & tag

imagePullSecrets

Registry access

6Ô∏è‚É£ Service & Networking Issues
kubectl get svc
kubectl describe svc <service-name>
kubectl get endpoints <service-name>


Check:

Selector mismatch

TargetPort mismatch

Pod readiness

7Ô∏è‚É£ Ingress Issues
kubectl get ingress
kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name>
kubectl logs <ingress-controller-pod>


Check:

TLS config

Path rules

Backend service mapping

8Ô∏è‚É£ Resource & Performance Issues
kubectl top nodes
kubectl top pods
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>


Check:

CPU throttling

Memory OOMKilled

Missing requests

9Ô∏è‚É£ HPA Issues
kubectl get hpa
kubectl describe hpa
kubectl top pods


Check:

Metrics server

CPU requests defined

HPA min/max limits

üîü Storage Issues
kubectl get pv
kubectl get pvc
kubectl describe pvc <pvc-name>


Check:

PVC Pending

Access modes

StorageClass

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Namespace & Quota Issues
kubectl get ns
kubectl get resourcequota
kubectl describe resourcequota

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Node Maintenance
kubectl cordon <node-name>
kubectl drain <node-name> --ignore-daemonsets --delete-emptydir-data
kubectl uncordon <node-name>
